  "riddle": "1. Seek the network that held the national cable rights for hockey in seasons past — which years did they dominate the ice?\n\n2. A channel known for its sports talk and lively coverage made its debut in the spring of which year?\n\n3. The telecommunications giant that operates from a vibrant city also shaped this channel — where is their home base found?\n\n4. If you gaze upon a map, how far does the ground rise beneath this bustling metropolis?\n\n5. Discover the count of sacred places of worship that gather around this same urban center.\n\n6. To proceed, find the absolute difference between the elevation you discovered in clue 4 and the number of temples you counted in clue 5.\n\n7. Tally the vowels in the name of the corporation you uncovered in clue 3 — how many do you find?\n\n8. In what year did the first auditory broadcast of a boxing clash resonate through radios in a significant Western city?\n\n9. Seek the financial threshold typically required for accessing a local sports channel’s feed in the year 2024 — what figure appears?\n\n10. The national broadcaster has a schedule of how many hours dedicated to its viewing audience?\n\n11. From the location of the broadcaster, how many places of worship do you find nearby?\n\n12. Count the hospitals that grace the vicinity of a historic abbey situated in Yorkshire.\n\n13. In which year did the channel synonymous with Canadian hockey first stake its claim to national cable rights for the NHL?\n\n14. When did the sports network linked with a prominent national contract join the ranks of NHL coverage?\n\n15. How many athletic arenas stand in proximity to this broadcast hub of hockey excitement?\n\n16. To continue, uncover the largest prime factor of the number you retrieved from clue 14.\n\n17. What is the total number of seasons this esteemed channel has devoted to broadcasting hockey games?\n\n18. At what age did the legendary sportscaster, known for his passionate commentary, leave this world?\n\n19. What height is attributed to the famous hockey commentator, represented in the data source?\n\n20. How many individuals call the land of the maple leaf their home?\n\n21. The next prime number after the population figure you found in clue 20 — what number emerges from your search?\n\n22. Finally, compute the expression: take the absolute difference between the figure from clue 6 and 1921, then apply modulo 10. The solution will yield a single digit!",
